CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1957, pg. A17 reads: "Enjoying Champagne from the silver fountain at the formal was this group of charming visitors. Left to right: Claude Dickson of Springfield, Mass. and Atlanta, Ga.; Dr. Mary Jane Watkins Evans, Ethel Wise Absalom, Maj. and Mrs. W.M. Roberts, all of New York City, and Henry Etheridge of Baltimore, Md."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Claude Dickson, Dr. Mary Jane Watkins Evans, Ethel Wise Absalom, Major and Mrs. W.M. Roberts, and Henry Etheridge, standing behind punch bowl table fountain, in Gateway Plaza for FROGS Formal Ball
